1
00:00:00,208 --> 00:00:02,002
I must be crazy.

2
00:00:02,002 --> 00:00:03,628
What was I imagining!

3
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:05,463
I think I'm drunk.

4
00:00:05,463 --> 00:00:07,757
I'll go first.

5
00:00:28,862 --> 00:00:29,779
Let's go together.

6
00:00:38,246 --> 00:00:39,539
You look drunk,

7
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:42,042
so I'm holding you in case you fall.

8
00:00:43,918 --> 00:00:46,671
I can't pretend I don't know anymore.

9
00:00:46,671 --> 00:00:49,090
Even though I know I shouldn't,

10
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:51,843
I keep wanting to get closer to you.

11
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:53,094
Hyung!

12
00:00:55,680 --> 00:00:56,723
Let's go.

13
00:00:56,723 --> 00:00:58,475
I'll walk you home.

14
00:01:16,409 --> 00:01:17,494
He's not here.

15
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,005
Contact me when you're sober.

16
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:30,006
Let's get some hangover soup.

17
00:01:32,217 --> 00:01:35,178
How can I contact him after what happened yesterday?

18
00:01:40,475 --> 00:01:42,060
What are you imagining?

19
00:01:47,982 --> 00:01:49,359
We definitely ki...

20
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:51,444
Ki?

21
00:01:51,945 --> 00:01:55,281
Ki... kissed...

22
00:01:57,909 --> 00:01:59,744
Han Jaemin, you're crazy.

23
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:01,579
You've completely lost your mind.

24
00:02:02,622 --> 00:02:04,916
It's so embarrassing, how can I face him?

25
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,417
I'm going off the grid.

26
00:02:06,417 --> 00:02:08,419
I shouldn't run into him for a while.

27
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:18,680
My jacket.

28
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,683
Where did my jacket go?

29
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:28,982
Ah, I have your jacket.

30
00:02:28,982 --> 00:02:30,441
Do you want to come get it?

31
00:02:31,776 --> 00:02:33,736
The interview is tomorrow...

32
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:37,365
That's the only jacket I have. What do I do?

33
00:02:59,304 --> 00:03:00,513
Are you shy?

34
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:02,307
Wh... What?

35
00:03:03,057 --> 00:03:04,642
I don't remember anything.

36
00:03:05,143 --> 00:03:07,312
I think you do remember.

37
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:08,563
Should I tell you?

38
00:03:09,397 --> 00:03:11,191
You had some strange imaginations,

39
00:03:11,399 --> 00:03:13,484
and you kissed my palm too.

40
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:14,694
And...

41
00:03:16,738 --> 00:03:18,364
Stop it.

42
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:20,033
I remember everything.

43
00:03:21,326 --> 00:03:23,953
Do you like receiving palm kisses too?

44
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,163
Are you asking me to do it?

45
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:27,040
It's not like that!

46
00:03:28,833 --> 00:03:30,335
I thought you were only cute when drunk,

47
00:03:30,335 --> 00:03:31,252
but I guess not.

48
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:32,295
Yes?

49
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:33,630
Nothing.

50
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,380
Here are the clothes.

51
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:48,144
It seems we are the same size.

52
00:03:48,144 --> 00:03:49,687
I don't know if it'll fit.

53
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:53,066
Why this?

54
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:55,235
So I can get you to buy me a drink this time.

55
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:58,279
Try it on.

56
00:03:58,279 --> 00:03:58,947
What?

57
00:03:59,280 --> 00:04:01,241
We need to check if it fits.

58
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,543
It looks expensive.

59
00:04:12,543 --> 00:04:14,879
Is it really okay for you to give this to me?

60
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:17,632
I won't be wearing it anymore, so it's fine.

61
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:20,343
Still...

62
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:22,679
I feel bad just taking it.

63
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:25,723
I'm not just giving it to you.

64
00:04:26,224 --> 00:04:28,643
I wish you would push me away instead.

65
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:31,312
I wish you'd tell me to stop.

66
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:37,193
The broken brake is acting up at a time like this.

67
00:04:37,443 --> 00:04:39,028
I told myself so many times

68
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:42,282
that I shouldn't get close to this person.

69
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:44,659
But my heart,

70
00:04:44,659 --> 00:04:46,953
my body,

71
00:04:46,953 --> 00:04:48,788
keeps wanting this person.

72
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,085
You're too close.

73
00:04:54,210 --> 00:04:55,837
We were closer back then.

74
00:04:56,337 --> 00:04:57,380
Back then...

75
00:05:00,091 --> 00:05:02,635
I'm not just giving this to you.

76
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:05,179
I'll use it cleanly and return it.

77
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:15,106
I told you, I'm not just giving it.

78
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:21,988
It seems the size fits perfectly.

79
00:05:22,530 --> 00:05:23,614
Yes.

80
00:05:32,165 --> 00:05:34,292
It might get wrinkled if you wear it like that.

81
00:05:54,228 --> 00:05:55,813
Do well.

82
00:05:55,813 --> 00:05:57,231
It will definitely go well this time.

83
00:05:57,398 --> 00:05:58,983
You can do it.

84
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:02,111
You're definitely going to pass this time.

85
00:06:05,865 --> 00:06:07,367
Mr. Han Jaemin?

86
00:06:08,701 --> 00:06:10,370
The prudence you claim as your strength

87
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:12,872
could be a weakness in our industry.

88
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:15,333
Given the nature of the industry where speed is life,

89
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,627
your work processing ability

90
00:06:17,627 --> 00:06:19,879
might not fit well with our company.

91
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:23,883
Did you write your cover letter knowing that?

92
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:28,388
Yes, I am well aware that speed is life.

93
00:06:28,388 --> 00:06:30,306
Nevertheless, I wrote it in my self-introduction

94
00:06:30,306 --> 00:06:33,851
because I judged that I have strengths to supplement that weakness.

95
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:35,937
You have strengths?

96
00:06:36,229 --> 00:06:39,524
I possess the ability to prevent accidents.

97
00:06:40,650 --> 00:06:42,151
If you only speed up,

98
00:06:42,151 --> 00:06:43,194
you might lose direction

99
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:45,488
or be unable to stop.

100
00:06:45,696 --> 00:06:47,990
The prudence I have

101
00:06:47,990 --> 00:06:51,077
will become a brake that finds the direction.

102
00:06:51,077 --> 00:06:52,495
It will be useful

103
00:06:52,495 --> 00:06:55,415
when finding the right path to avoid accidents.

104
00:06:56,374 --> 00:06:58,543
Should I take that as you'll work hard?

105
00:06:58,668 --> 00:06:59,293
No.

106
00:06:59,710 --> 00:07:01,045
I will do well.

107
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:03,798
I will achieve more than you expect.

108
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:09,637
You keep touching your clothes.

109
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:11,389
Is there something uncomfortable?

110
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:16,018
I was in the middle of steadying my mind.

111
00:07:16,018 --> 00:07:19,355
These clothes were lent to me by someone who recognized my strengths.

112
00:07:19,730 --> 00:07:21,691
Someone who recognized your strengths?

113
00:07:21,858 --> 00:07:22,608
Yes.

114
00:07:23,192 --> 00:07:25,027
Like this stiffly raised shirt collar,

115
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:26,863
he gave me courage

116
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:28,656
not to be discouraged in front of the interviewer.

117
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:32,577
He reminded me of the importance of my strengths and prudence.

118
00:07:33,161 --> 00:07:35,413
Thanks to that, I didn't lose heart

119
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:37,874
and could answer confidently in front of you.

120
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:39,459
I have to earn the worth of these clothes.

121
00:07:40,042 --> 00:07:40,918
Interesting.

122
00:07:41,294 --> 00:07:42,253
But would you have that guts

123
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,880
wearing your own clothes?

124
00:07:44,088 --> 00:07:44,589
Pardon?

125
00:07:44,964 --> 00:07:46,048
You may leave.

126
00:07:46,048 --> 00:07:47,133
Good news will come.

127
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,886
Yes.

128
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:52,555
Thank you.

129
00:07:58,269 --> 00:08:00,521
I like that he's spirited.
